						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">UncleSporky wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">That's very interesting.  Must've been quite tricky for them to fit it all in.</div>
<br />Well, with CHR-RAM they don't have to worry much about tile usage, since only the characters being displayed need to be loaded. It sure needs more PRG-ROM than the average font though... but still probably not much, specially if compression is used. The most obvious compression would be to only store one plane of the tiles, since the text is black and white.</div>

